    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect TDD configuration and frequency settings in signal analyzer\n\n### Summary\nThe LTE signal analyzer function had multiple configuration issues that caused it to behave unexpectedly when analyzing TDD signals. The analyzer was hardcoded to 1.2GHz regardless of the actual carrier frequency, used incorrect GPIB commands for TDD special subframe configuration, and didn't properly utilize the DCI allocation information passed to it.\n\nThis fix corrects the frequency configuration, fixes the TDD special subframe commands, and properly uses the DCI allocation parameters.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/SIMULATION/LTE_PHY/signalanalyzer.c`: \n  * Fixed carrier frequency to use `frame_parms->dl_CarrierFreq` instead of hardcoded 1.2GHz\n  * Changed TDD special subframe configuration command from `CONF:DL:TDD:UDC` to `CONF:DL:TDD:SSC`\n  * Added NULL check for frame parameters\n  * Added proper usage of DCI allocation RNTI parameter\n  * Fixed format specifier for rnti_t from %d to %u\n- `openair1/SIMULATION/LTE_PHY/signalanalyzer.h`: \n  * Fixed include from \"PHY/defs.h\" to \"PHY/defs_common.h\"\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure a TDD LTE system with a carrier frequency other than 1.2GHz\n2. Run the signal analyzer function with valid frame parameters and DCI allocation\n3. Observe that the analyzer is configured to 1.2GHz instead of the actual carrier frequency\n4. Notice that TDD special subframe configuration commands fail due to incorrect command syntax\n5. See that the DCI allocation RNTI information is ignored\n\nThe incorrect configuration will cause the signal analyzer to produce inaccurate measurements or fail to decode PDCCH properly.\n"
}